      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(google): route Gemma models through native Generative AI API",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nGemma models (gemma-4-31b-it, gemma-4-26b-it, etc.) fail silently when used through the Google provider. The OpenAI-compatible endpoint (`/v1beta/openai/chat/completions`) returns 400/401 errors for Gemma models — only the native Generative AI endpoint works.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nIn `provider-models.ts`, Gemma models clone from the `gemini-3-flash-preview` template and inherit its `api` field (typically `openai-completions`). But Gemma only supports the native Google Generative AI API format.\n\n## Fix\n\nForce `api: \"google-generative-ai\"` in the Gemma branch of `resolveGoogleGeminiForwardCompatModel`, so Gemma models use the existing native transport (`transport-stream.ts` → `buildGoogleRequestUrl` → `/v1beta/models/{model}:streamGenerateContent`).\n\n## Change\n\n```diff\n } else if (lower.startsWith(GEMMA_PREFIX)) {\n     family = {\n       googleTemplateIds: GEMMA_TEMPLATE_IDS,\n       cliTemplateIds: GEMMA_TEMPLATE_IDS,\n     };\n+    // Gemma models only support the native Google Generative AI API;\n+    // the OpenAI-compatible endpoint does not serve Gemma.\n+    patch = { api: \"google-generative-ai\" as ProviderRuntimeModel[\"api\"] };\n     if (lower.startsWith(\"gemma-4\")) {\n-      patch = { reasoning: true };\n+      patch.reasoning = true;\n     }\n```\n\n## Testing\n\n- Direct curl to native endpoint confirmed working\n- OpenAI-compat endpoint confirmed failing for Gemma\n\nFixes #68984\nRelated: #61501, #63685",
        "branch": "fix/gemma-native-api",
